  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely. Money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (often referred to as \"dirty money\") appear legal (or \"clean\") by disguising the true origin of the funds. This is typically done through a series of complex transactions designed to obscure the source of the money.\n\nMost jurisdictions have stringent laws and regulations in place to combat money laundering, often requiring financial institutions and other businesses to implement measures to detect and report suspicious activities. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including significant fines, asset seizure, and imprisonment.\n\nIn short, money laundering is a serious crime with serious consequences.",
